The paper discusses the use of spectral imaging for face recognition in biometric systems, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning-based methods, which is a popular topic in the machine learning (cs.MM) sub-category. The challenges and advancements in the field of spectral imaging for face recognition also involve issues related to information retrieval (cs.IR), cryptography (cs.CR), and statistical learning (cs.LG), which are all relevant sub-categories.
